02:20:23.70 --> 02:20:28.42
And as that guy starts to sweep back, goes up.

1816
02:20:28.42 --> 02:20:32.46
And immediately, huge ambush.

1817
02:20:32.46 --> 02:20:35.26
I mean, just firing from everywhere.

1818
02:20:35.26 --> 02:20:38.34
And this is this unit's first time in contact.

1819
02:20:38.34 --> 02:20:41.74
So they're just heads down, just not looking where they're

1820
02:20:41.74 --> 02:20:45.66
firing, just blossom, shooting everywhere.

1821
02:20:45.66 --> 02:20:48.70
And there's only one Marine who's standing up, running

1822
02:20:48.70 --> 02:20:50.86
into the field to go get the guy who got this blown up.

1823
02:20:50.86 --> 02:20:54.06
And it's Sergeant Decker, the guy who just said a few minutes

1824
02:20:54.06 --> 02:20:55.38
